                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mid-nineteenth/mid-twentieth century bulky script</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black (on many folia brownish); vivid red.</seg>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Divine names; directives to the ministers; titles of books to be read; elements of the punctuation signs;
                           elements of the Ethiopic numerals. On the incipit page of <ref target="#p1_i1">Text 1</ref>, <locus target="#8r"/>
                           two first lines of each column are rubricated. Rubrication has been carefully executed in the main
                           hand, probably along with the writing of the main text.</seg>
                           <desc>Text written in a smaller tighten script.
                             Starting from ca. <locus target="#47"/>, the handwriting becomes less careful; on <locus from="50r" to="51r"/>
                             the scribe squeezed more written lines than the ruling allows, slightly reducing the size of the script.
                           </desc>
                     </handNote>

                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic"> Hand b: quire I (<locus from="3r" to="6r">3r-6r</locus>).<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
